You are creating a Bash script of user information. Which of the following commands printsthe username and real name of all users in /etc/passwd in a tab- separated format?
A)  cut - d: - f 1,6 /etc/passwd
B)  sed 's/://' /etc/passwd
C)  awk - F: '{print $1,$5}' OFS="\t" /etc/passwd
D)  cat - o "\t" /etc/passwd
C
C. The awk command shown can be used for this purpose. The - F option sets the field sepa-rator, and the OFS option sets the output field separator.
